# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/

# app.wranngle.com is the canonical console host. The bare landing
# (apps/ops-console/index.html) used to be a marketing middleman —
# operators clicked through it to reach /console/. Skip it: bare-root
# visits go straight to /console/ on whatever host they arrived on
# (app.wranngle.com OR the gtm-ops.pages.dev preview host). Pages
# `_redirects` rules are path-only, so we can't host-discriminate
# here without a Pages Function — and we don't need to: redirecting
# to a relative /console/ works on every host, and avoids the
# self-loop we'd hit if `/` on app.wranngle.com 301'd to
# https://app.wranngle.com/. Direct paths (/console/, /eval-runs/)
# still serve as before.
/                 /console/                   301
/index.html       /console/                   301

# No /api/* rules here on purpose: functions/api/[[path]].ts is the
# catch-all for unported routes (fixture fallback on preview hosts, honest
# JSON 404 on production). The old `/api/* → /fixtures/:splat.json 302`
# wildcard fired on the production host too, converting unported-route 404s
# into 200s of demo data. The JS shim in each HTML page still intercepts
# /api/* client-side on DEMO_MODE hosts.
